# WHAT IT IS
#   The classical pattern for adding GraphQL to an organization that
#   has invested in REST APIs is the **GraphQL gateway / wrapper /
#   fa├¦ade**:  build a GraphQL server that accepts GraphQL queries +
#   mutations from clients, dispatches each typed resolver to the
#   underlying REST microservice, and returns the merged response.
#   Hand-authoring this wrapper is tedious + error-prone because:
#
#     ŌĆó Every REST resource needs a typed GraphQL ObjectType
#     ŌĆó Every REST endpoint needs a typed Query or Mutation
#       resolver
#     ŌĆó Every REST authentication header / query parameter / path
#       parameter needs to be mapped to a typed GraphQL argument
#     ŌĆó REST status codes need to be mapped to GraphQL errors
#     ŌĆó Pagination conventions (offset, cursor, page+size) need
#       canonicalization
#     ŌĆó Cross-resource references (foreign keys in REST URLs) need
#       to be turned into typed GraphQL link fields
#
#   `openapi-to-graphql` automates the entire transformation by
#   reading the **OpenAPI Specification** (OAS) ŌĆö the standard
#   machine-readable description of a REST API (formerly Swagger;
#   maintained by the OpenAPI Initiative under the Linux
#   Foundation) ŌĆö and emitting a typed GraphQL schema where:
#
#     ŌĆó Each typed `components/schemas/Foo` JSON Schema becomes a
#       typed GraphQL ObjectType with the same fields
#     ŌĆó Each `GET /foo/{id}` operation becomes a typed Query
#       resolver `foo(id: ID!): Foo`
#     ŌĆó Each `POST /foo` operation becomes a typed Mutation
#       resolver `createFoo(input: FooInput!): Foo`
#     ŌĆó Each `PUT / PATCH / DELETE` operation becomes a typed
#       Mutation resolver with appropriate name conventions
#     ŌĆó Each REST authentication scheme (`apiKey`, `oauth2`,
#       `http basic`, `http bearer`) becomes a typed GraphQL
#       `viewer` argument that clients pass at the root query
#       level
#     ŌĆó Resolvers internally use `cross-fetch` to call the
#       underlying REST endpoint
#
#   Two operation modes:
#
#     ŌĆó **Live server mode** (default) ŌĆö boots an express-graphql
#       server on `--port <PORT>` (default 3000) that serves the
#       generated schema; clients can immediately hit it with
#       GraphiQL / Apollo Sandbox / Postman / curl
#
#     ŌĆó **Save schema mode** (`--save <FILE>`) ŌĆö generates the
#       SDL schema file and exits without starting a server.
#       Useful for emitting the schema as a build artifact for
#       downstream Apollo Federation / schema-registry tooling.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from packages/openapi-to-graphql-
#                       cli/src/index.ts commander.js
#                       registration; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       packages/openapi-to-graphql-cli/src/
#                       index.ts)
#
#   openapi-to-graphql <OAS_PATH_OR_URL>... [OPTIONS]
#
#   Positional:
#     OAS_PATH_OR_URL...             One or more OpenAPI
#                                    Specification (OAS) JSON or
#                                    YAML files ŌĆö local paths or
#                                    HTTPS URLs are both accepted
#                                    (multiple OAS files are
#                                    merged into a single GraphQL
#                                    schema)
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#     -s, --strict                   Throw an error if openapi-
#                                    to-graphql cannot run
#                                    without compensating for
#                                    errors / missing data in
#                                    the OAS (default: silently
#                                    work around OAS issues)
#     --save <FILE>                  Save the generated GraphQL
#                                    SDL schema to <FILE> and
#                                    exit (default: start a
#                                    live express-graphql
#                                    server)
#
#   Server options:
#     -p, --port <PORT>              Port for the live server
#                                    [default: 3000]
#     -u, --url <URL>                Override the base URL that
#                                    resolvers will call (default
#                                    is the OAS `servers[]`
#                                    field)
#     --cors                         Enable CORS on the live
#                                    server
#
#   Schema options:
#     -o, --operationIdFieldNames    Generate field names based
#                                    on each operation's
#                                    `operationId` field instead
#                                    of the inferred name
#     -f, --fillEmptyResponses       Generate placeholder schemas
#                                    for operations with no
#                                    response body (default
#                                    behavior is to omit them)
#     --addLimitArgument             Add a `limit` argument on
#                                    fields returning lists for
#                                    client-side data-size
#                                    control
#     --genericPayloadArgName        Set the mutation payload
#                                    argument name to
#                                    `requestBody` instead of
#                                    the operation-specific
#                                    name
#     --simpleNames                  Only remove illegal
#                                    characters from OAS names;
#                                    ignore casing + formatting
#     --simpleEnumValues             Only remove illegal
#                                    characters from OAS enum
#                                    values
#     --singularNames                Experimental: create more
#                                    meaningful names from the
#                                    operation path
#
#   Resolver options:
#     -H, --header <KEY:VAL>         Add a header to every
#                                    resolver REST call
#                                    (repeatable; `key:value`
#                                    notation)
#     -Q, --queryString <KEY:VAL>    Add a query parameter to
#                                    every resolver REST call
#                                    (repeatable)
#
#   Authentication options:
#     --no-viewer                    Do NOT create GraphQL viewer
#                                    objects for authentication
#                                    credentials (default is to
#                                    create one viewer per OAS
#                                    security scheme)
#
#   Logging options:
#     --no-extensions                Do NOT add `extensions` (with
#                                    info about failed REST
#                                    calls) to GraphQL error
#                                    objects
#     --no-equivalentToMessages      Do NOT append "Equivalent to
#                                    <REST operation>" hints to
#                                    field descriptions
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `IBM/openapi-to-graphql-cli` declares a **direct** dependency
#   on `graphql@^16.5.0` AND `openapi-to-graphql` (the IBM-
#   maintained core library) in its `package.json` (verified via
#   `gh api repos/IBM/openapi-to-graphql/contents/packages/
