#       AST traversal
#     ŌĆó Typed extension utilities ŌĆö `Source`, `Location`,
#       `Token`, `Lexer`, `getLocation`, `printLocation`,
#       `printSourceLocation`
#
#   GraphQL itself was invented at **Facebook** in 2012 by Lee
#   Byron, Nick Schrock, and Daniel Schafer to solve REST's
#   over-fetching / under-fetching / endpoint-proliferation
#   problems.  Internal at Facebook through 2014 (used to power
#   the Facebook iOS + Android apps' News Feed, Messenger,
#   Search, Notifications) before being open-sourced in 2015
#   alongside `graphql-js`.  Standardized as the **GraphQL
#   Specification (October 2018 + subsequent releases)** by the
#   **GraphQL Foundation** (Linux Foundation member organization)
#   in 2019.
#
#   Architecture:
#
#     ŌĆó **Schema** ŌĆö typed `.graphql` SDL files defining Query
#       / Mutation / Subscription root types + their typed
#       nested ObjectType / InputObjectType / Interface /
#       Union / Enum / Scalar primitives
#     ŌĆó **Resolvers** ŌĆö per-field functions that fetch data on
#       demand (the canonical solution to REST over-fetching)
#     ŌĆó **Single endpoint** ŌĆö typically `/graphql` over POST
#       (HTTP/1.1 + HTTP/2 + HTTP/3) carrying the GraphQL query
#       document
#     ŌĆó **Subscriptions** ŌĆö bidirectional real-time updates
#       over WebSocket (`graphql-ws` or legacy `subscriptions-
#       transport-ws` protocols) or HTTP/2 SSE
#     ŌĆó **Fragments** ŌĆö composable query reuse
#     ŌĆó **Directives** ŌĆö `@include(if: ...)`, `@skip(if: ...)`,
#       `@deprecated(reason: ...)`, `@specifiedBy(url)`, plus
#       custom directives
#     ŌĆó **Introspection** ŌĆö typed `__schema` /  `__type(name:
#       ...)` queries for runtime schema discovery (powers
#       GraphiQL, Apollo Sandbox, Insomnia, Postman, Banana Cake
#       Pop, every modern GraphQL IDE)
#     ŌĆó **Apollo Federation** ŌĆö service composition layer for
#       splitting a single supergraph across multiple subgraph
#       services (the dominant GraphQL gateway pattern; powers
#       GitHub's, Shopify's, Atlassian's, Netflix's, Uber's, and
#       Airbnb's GraphQL gateways)
#
#   Verified via:
